<p class="text-center" style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;">--Shopping in Gwalior--</p>
<span>While traveling to the beautiful city of Gwalior make sure to enjoy every bit of your journey!Apart from beautiful historical monuments and sites the city is dotted with numerous market ares and malls.
As tourist you will be able to get a wide variety of shopping items from the city. Never miss to take away traditional Gwalior handicrafts and other beautiful items.</span><br><br>
<div class="text-center">
    <img src="./resources/img/shopping.jpg" alt="">
</div>
<p>-What to buy in Gwalior?</p>
<span><b>Handlooms:</b> The trademark of Gwalior’s handloom industry includes the delicate and light cotton and silk saris such as Maheshwari and Chanderi. These saris are readily available in Kothari at Sarafa Bazaar for their brocade and silk saris.
This store is popular for selling genuine staff shop rates high in terms of customer satisfaction. You will also be able to find these saris in the nearby shop of MP Khadi Sangh where you can consider being an excellent option for exploring handlooms.
</span><br><br>
<div class="text-center">
    <img src="./resources/img/shopping2.jpg" alt="">
</div><br><br>

<span><b>Wholesale clothes:</b> Those of you who wish to purchase wholesale clothes from the wholesale clothes market, then you need to go further as these are readily available in the Naya Bazaar, Dahi Mandi and also in the Gandhi Bazaar areas.</span><br><br>
<span><b>Jewelry:</b>Jewelry is one item which is considered to be the women’s most favored item. Asides from this it also adds to the family’s wealth. In order to shop for your Jewelry item, you can try Mangalam Jewelers and Tanishq which are both located in Sarafa Bazaar, while Anand Jewelers and A.P. Jewelers are to be found in the famous Laskar market.</span><br><br>
<span>Beautiful designer jewelry is quite famous in Gwalior. With their beutiful look and appeal they attract every eye. Patankar bazaar is famous for its shops dealing in designer jewelry.</span><br><br> 
<div class="text-center">
    <img src="./resources/img/shopping3.jpg" alt="">
</div><br><br>    

<span><b>Handicrafts and Artifacts:</b> Since Gwalior has a rich cultural legacy, this factor is also reflected in the cities brilliantly and unique designed handicrafts.</span><br><br>
<span>You will also be able to get artistic stone carvings and artifacts which will range from bags and leather products right down to the innovative silk and woolen carpets. This is the reason as to why the handicrafts of Gwalior are a flourishing one. You will be able to find these items in Subhash Market’s famous shop of MD Fine Arts for their amazing paintings.</span><br><br>

<span>Moreover, from Very Arihant Emporium, you will be able to purchase lovely silver boxes which have been decorated with images. This store is near Jai Villas Palace.</span><br><br>

<span>Besides these amazing specialties, in Gwalior you will be able to find all of the conventional shopping items which are on display in its hundreds of shops.</span><br><br>

<h5>Shopping destinations in Gwalior</h5>
<h6>Arihant Emporium in Gwalior</h6>
<div class="text-center">
    <img src="./resources/img/shopping4.jpg" alt="">
</div><br><br>

<span>In this wonderful emporium, you will be able to by many eye-catching items like hand-woven saris, jute crafts, silverware, dokra figurines, brassware, and tribal wooden jewelry.</span><br><br>
<span>Asides form the women even the men visit this place out of curiosity. The most popular purchasing item in this emporium is the emporium’s miniature stone-carved erotic sculptures of Khajuraho. The emporium is located at Moti
Mahal Road Old Town near Jai Vilas Palace.</span><br><br><br>

<span>Arihant Emporium</span><br>
<span>Address: Roshni Ghar Mohalla, Lashkar, Gwalior,</span><br>
<span>Madhya Pradesh 474009</span><br><br>

<h5>Patankar Bazaar in Gwalior</h5>
<span>It is a very famous shopping place in Gwalior. On walking down the street, you will come across many shop vendors greeting you with friendly smile. One thing is sure that you will obviously look at their wares and may even end buying something.</span><br><br>
<span>The most popular shopping items here are: ornaments, dolls, lacquer ware, wall hangings, and handmade carpets. An absolute must-have for every woman is the ever popular Chanderi saris found here is. So, you should not forget to shop for some while walking down the alleys of this popular bazaar.</span><br><br>

<h5>Sarafa Bazaar in Gwalior</h5>
<span>It is one of the most crowded markets of Gwalior which is always bustling with activity until the late nights. It is here that you will be able to shop for Chanderi silks, brocade and Silk saris and handloom products. Sarafa Bazar located in the Lashkar area of Gwalior is a must visit shopping destination in the historical city.</span><br><br>


<h5>Bada Naya Bazaar in Gwalior</h5>
<span>Both of these bazaars are popular places for their Maheshwari and Chanderi and saris as well as handicraft items. You will be able to shop for beautiful articles and products which have been crafted from paper Mache. Women as well as men come to shop in these markets.</span><br><br>
<span>This bazaar is also bustling with activity till the late evenings with busy shoppers. Here, you will be able to come across local eatery shops the bazaar’s many hotels which are dotted in the streets of this famous bazaar just in case you feel hungry after shopping.</span><br><br>


<h5>Topi Bazaar in Gwalior</h5>
<span>This bazaar is near around Sarafa Bazaar which is equally vibrant. It is also a complete shopper’s haven. Availability of long lasting leather products makes the tiny market area famous in Gwalior. From Sneakers to Bags and Purses all and more can be found in this part of Gwalior. Young ladoes often throng to this market to buy leather made sandals and designer bags. Small designer purses are yet another item found in this part of Gwalior.</span><br><br>

<h5>Dindayal City Mall in Gwalior</h5>
<div class="text-center">
    <img src="./resources/img/shopping5.jpg" alt="">
</div><br><br> 
<span>The spacious mall is located in the heart of Gwalior and attract youngsters and tourists in huge numbers. It is amongst one of the biggest mall of Madhya Pradesh. It serves as an excellent shopping destination and is an ideal place for purchasing branded items such as electronic items, branded apparels, designer jewelry and home accessories.
</span><br><br>
<span>While shopping if you wish to have a quick bite then you can head straight to the pizza hut or McDonalds. Being centrally air-conditioned this lively mall is an ideal place for hanging out with friends and family.
</span><br><br>
<h5><b>Dindayal City Mall</b></h5>
<span><b>Address:</b> Opposite Gurudwara, Mlb Road, Lashkar City, Gwalior - 474009</span><br><br>
<span>So whenever the next time traveling to Gwalior do not forget to visit the above mentioned shopping destinations for purchasing high end goods and other popular items.</span>




